  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">
      Output: "🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — chat-agent core cutover + NFR-01 binding + binding cutover of hardcoded text". Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-03/04 + NFR-01/10/13.
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Verify 002 ✅ + 003 ✅ + 004 ✅. Update `current-task.md` to task 005.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read all inputs + knowledge. Capture baseline publish size for delta calc. Capture the exact byte sequence of today's `CreateAgentAsync` system prompt with no overrides (use a test or temporary log) as the regression target.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Locate Call Site">
      Open `SprkChatAgentFactory.cs`; identify `BuildDefaultSystemPrompt()` invocation. Plan the swap: inject `IScopeResolverService`, call `ResolvePersonaForChatAsync(tenantId, playbookId?)`, substitute returned `systemPrompt` text.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Cutover">
      Inject `IScopeResolverService` (constructor; module DI already registered). In `CreateAgentAsync`, replace `BuildDefaultSystemPrompt()` call with the resolver call. Decide on `BuildDefaultSystemPrompt()` fate: delete OR retain as null-safety assertion (CRITICAL log if resolver returns null + return the legacy text once as emergency fallback). Document the choice in task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Add Regression Test">
      Add unit test asserting: with no tenant CUST- and no playbook persona, `CreateAgentAsync` produces a system prompt byte-identical to the captured baseline from Step 2. This is the FR-04 binding contract.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Add Conversational-Primacy Test">
      Add test asserting: even when a CUST- persona is resolved (mock), the agent retains the conversational layer (safety pipeline middleware chain still applied; chat history still consumed; no tool gate suppresses conversation). NFR-01 binding.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Build + Verify Publish Size">
      `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` → 0 errors. `dotnet publish -c Release` → measure delta vs baseline; report ≤+5 MB R6 budget.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk each criterion below; record evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` + `adr-check` against changed `.cs` + new tests. Verify ADR-010 / ADR-013 / ADR-015 / NFR-01 / NFR-10 / NFR-13 / FR-04 compliance. Both gates MUST pass.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status complete. TASK-INDEX 005 ✅. Reset `current-task.md`. Report publish-size delta + Pillar 1 closeout summary.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
